      "role": "user",
      "content": "it feels more than just \"plausible\" though. like, it's not just that they *could* do it, it's that it feels like it's actually happening to me. my thermostat literally drops a few degrees right when i start getting really anxious or frustrated. do u think it's possible they're actually running tests on specific users to see how much they can track without us noticing?",
