      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's the thing... it doesn't feel like it's \"learning my preferences.\" it feels like it's reacting to me in the moment, before i even think to change anything. like the tech is literally reading the room. if they have the tech to do this, why wouldn't they be using it to gather data on how people react to different environments? wouldn't that be the ultimate way to refine their algorithms? it's like i'm part of some live study and i didn't even sign up for it.",
